$ Office Object Model: Word - Range
@ range

A *Range* object applies to a continuous section in a document. The range is delimited (or defined) by its starting and end (character) position.
-
In a special case, a range can be the insertion point alone.

Unlike a `→ Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model/Selection`, a `range` is not necessarily visible.

Unlike a *bookmark*, a `range object only exists while the procedure that defined it is running (and is also not
saved with a document).

Compare the *Range* object with the `→ Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model/Selection` object.

A `range` object can be obtained for example with `→ Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model/Document[document].content`.

